  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: Empty suggestion window stays on screen upon entering non-existing command in 1-1/group/public messagebox. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nEmpty suggestion window hides on screen upon entering non-existing command in 1-1/group/public messagebox\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nEmpty suggestion window stays on screen upon entering non-existing command in 1-1/group/public messagebox\r\n![image uploaded from ios](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/35624880-f8f237d6-0698-11e8-941b-337ab344cccb.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Navigate to 1-1chat with Jarrad\r\n- Put cursor in message editbox\r\n- Type the command starting with the slash that does not exist as an option for this chat (e.g. type `/brot`\r\n- Check if the empty window persist staying above message editbox\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information \r\n* Status version: release 0.9.13, latest develop  0.9.11d621 / g8f1bc58b+\r\n* Operating System: Android 7.0, iOS 11.2.2\r\n\r\nTF session: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/7608181/sessions/2/?accessToken=lEyMDZb-ylaZp8-ZudgrmLunmEA\r\n\r\n### Additional Information 2\r\nThe good example of what we need here is the behavior in Console chat when typing web3's non-existing methods. See the steps:\r\n1) Open Status \r\n2) Navigate to chat with 'Console'\r\n3) Type `web3.` (Note: the list of available options appeared)\r\n4) Proceed typing with `vero`\r\n5) Check if the window closed ",
